04:21.087 --> 04:23.322
Alan!

04:25.792 --> 04:27.593
Ow!

04:38.405 --> 04:39.839
Everything okay?

04:39.841 --> 04:42.708
Oh, yeah.
I think it just overheated.

04:42.710 --> 04:44.543
Can I give you a ride
to a gas station?

04:44.545 --> 04:47.113
Gee, I don't know.
My mom always told me

04:47.115 --> 04:49.949
never to get in a car
with a stranger.

04:49.951 --> 04:53.220
I'm Shari McMartin.

04:53.222 --> 04:55.322
Solves that problem.

04:55.824 --> 04:58.192
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

04:58.194 --> 05:00.327
Thank you.
I really appreciate it.

05:00.329 --> 05:02.429
Oh, no problem.

05:02.431 --> 05:04.666
So your old Volvo's
seen better days, huh?

05:04.668 --> 05:07.102
Yeah, it's actually,
it's not mine.

05:07.104 --> 05:09.905
I borrowed it from a friend
to get my bike fixed.

05:09.907 --> 05:11.540
You ride a bike around town.

05:11.542 --> 05:14.042
You must have
amazing stamina.

05:14.044 --> 05:17.779
Well, it's not the only way
that I get around.

05:17.781 --> 05:19.481
Hey, it's nothing
to be ashamed about.

05:19.483 --> 05:21.216
With the price of gas
being what it is,

05:21.218 --> 05:23.518
a bicycle is
very practical.

05:23.520 --> 05:26.488
I'm-I'm not ashamed.

05:26.490 --> 05:28.423
Trust me, there will come a day
when you won't have

05:28.425 --> 05:31.258
to worry about having enough
money for gas.

05:31.260 --> 05:34.094
Okay.

05:34.096 --> 05:36.063
I look forward to that day.

05:36.065 --> 05:38.632
So what's your name?

05:38.634 --> 05:40.401
Walden.

05:40.403 --> 05:41.936
That's a nice name.

05:41.938 --> 05:44.071
What are you doing in
Los Angeles, Walden?

05:44.073 --> 05:48.208
You trying to be an actor
or a model or something?

05:50.045 --> 05:55.149
Right now I'm trying
to finish a book.

05:55.151 --> 05:57.518
Oh. How long
have you been at it?

05:57.520 --> 05:59.387
14 years.

05:59.389 --> 06:01.856
Oh, a struggling writer.

06:03.492 --> 06:06.460
Yes. Yes, I am.

06:06.462 --> 06:07.795
Well, you are in luck.

06:07.797 --> 06:09.697
I happen to be a big
supporter of the arts.

06:09.699 --> 06:12.500
Oh, really?
How fortuitous.

06:12.502 --> 06:14.135
Ooh, "fortuitous."

06:14.137 --> 06:16.139
You <i>are</i> a writer.

06:16.141 --> 06:19.008
Listen, what do you say we
go grab a bite to eat,

06:19.010 --> 06:20.443
get the car fixed later?

06:20.445 --> 06:24.381
Sure. There's a really
great deli right up here.

06:24.383 --> 06:26.616
Well, actually, I have
a better place in mind.

06:26.618 --> 06:27.818
Where's that?

06:27.820 --> 06:29.053
My house.

06:29.055 --> 06:32.923
Oh. What's on the menu there?

06:34.225 --> 06:36.427
Oh.

06:36.429 --> 06:38.730
Yum.
Mm.

06:40.432 --> 06:43.067
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

06:43.069 --> 06:44.268
Hi.

06:44.270 --> 06:45.403
Hi.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.104
Whatcha doing?

06:47.106 --> 06:48.572
Nothing much.

06:48.574 --> 06:50.675
How about we go out to a movie?

06:50.677 --> 06:52.810
Sure, we could do that.
Great, great.

06:52.812 --> 06:54.578
I will check some times.

06:54.580 --> 06:56.380
Alan.
Yeah?

06:56.382 --> 06:58.750
Did you think about what we
discussed last night?

06:58.752 --> 07:00.551
Oh, yes, oh, yes.

07:00.553 --> 07:02.586
Thinking about it constantly.

07:02.588 --> 07:04.555
Anything you want to talk about?

07:04.557 --> 07:05.956
Not yet.

07:05.958 --> 07:08.025
Still thinking.

07:08.027 --> 07:10.962
You know, percolating,
uh, mulling.

07:10.964 --> 07:13.231
All the pertinent "ings."

07:13.233 --> 07:14.866
Ooh!

07:14.868 --> 07:16.935
Cogitating!

07:16.937 --> 07:19.571
Stalling, avoiding, ducking.

07:19.573 --> 07:21.040
Ooh! Procrastinating.

07:21.042 --> 07:23.075
What? No.

07:23.077 --> 07:24.110
That's-that's crazy.

07:24.112 --> 07:25.978
I'm not doing any
of those things.

07:25.980 --> 07:27.647
I mean, why would I do
those things?

07:27.649 --> 07:29.449
So what movie would you
like to see?

07:29.451 --> 07:31.484
I know what you're doing.

07:31.486 --> 07:32.886
This is not gonna go away.

07:32.888 --> 07:34.154
I just don't understand

07:34.156 --> 07:35.889
why we can't keep things
the way they are.

07:35.891 --> 07:37.257
You mean, living day-to-day,

07:37.259 --> 07:39.893
never knowing what kind of
future you have with the person

07:39.895 --> 07:42.229
you've been in a relationship
with the past three years?

07:42.231 --> 07:45.598
I prefer to think of it
as cherishing each day,

07:45.600 --> 07:48.001
nay each moment,
with the woman I love

07:49.070 --> 07:51.204
because none of us knows
how much time we have left.

07:51.206 --> 07:54.808
I mean, it could all disappear
in the blink of an eye.

07:54.810 --> 07:56.509
You mean like this?

07:58.980 --> 08:00.847
Exactly.

08:00.849 --> 08:03.416
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

08:03.418 --> 08:05.185
Well, it would appear
that a bicycle's

08:05.187 --> 08:07.119
not the only thing
you can ride.

08:07.121 --> 08:11.089
I'm also good with bulls
and merry-go-rounds.

08:11.091 --> 08:13.726
So, did you enjoy
your lunch?

08:13.728 --> 08:15.761
Oh, yeah.

08:15.763 --> 08:17.830
I would definitely
eat here again.

08:20.567 --> 08:22.200
Mm, mm.

08:24.136 --> 08:26.004
Do you mind
taking a taxi home?

08:27.339 --> 08:30.341
Uh, sure, no problem.

08:30.343 --> 08:33.409
I'd drive you, I just
have some things to do.

08:33.412 --> 08:35.645
Okay.

08:35.648 --> 08:38.482
So... then we're done here?

08:38.484 --> 08:40.417
I am.

08:40.419 --> 08:42.553
Okay.

08:42.554 --> 08:44.354
All righty then.

08:47.358 --> 08:49.226
You know, uh,
we should do this again.

08:49.228 --> 08:50.560
Oh, we will.

08:50.562 --> 08:51.995
I'll let you know when.

08:51.997 --> 08:54.297
All righty.

08:54.299 --> 08:56.500
Oh, here.

08:58.636 --> 09:00.037
What's this?

09:00.039 --> 09:01.538
It's money for a taxi.

09:01.540 --> 09:02.673
I don't need that.

09:02.675 --> 09:05.542
Sweetie, don't be proud.
Take the money.

09:08.346 --> 09:10.480
Okay, great.

09:12.150 --> 09:13.350
Thank you.

09:13.352 --> 09:14.985
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

09:20.918 --> 09:22.519
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

09:23.822 --> 09:25.055
Hey, hey!

09:25.057 --> 09:27.323
Hey. Where've you been?

09:27.325 --> 09:31.194
I got some good news
and I got some bad news for ya.

09:31.196 --> 09:32.295
What's the bad news?

09:32.297 --> 09:34.697
Your car overheated
and broke down.

09:34.699 --> 09:37.433
Ah, I should have told you
not to turn on the radio.

09:39.503 --> 09:41.437
So, uh, what's the good news?

09:41.439 --> 09:43.038
This beautiful woman pulls up

09:43.040 --> 09:45.407
in a Bentley and offers me help,

09:45.409 --> 09:47.108
and then she takes me back
to her house

09:47.110 --> 09:49.077
and bangs my brains out.

09:49.079 --> 09:51.713
How is that good news for me?

09:51.715 --> 09:52.980
Oh, sorry, I misspoke.

09:52.982 --> 09:56.217
The bad news was for you,
the good news was for me.

09:56.219 --> 09:57.918
Do you have any idea
how many times

09:57.920 --> 09:59.753
I've been stranded by the side
of the road 'cause of that car?

09:59.755 --> 10:01.388
The only person who's ever
stopped was a truck driver

10:01.390 --> 10:03.757
with no pants
and drawn-on eyebrows.

10:03.759 --> 10:05.926
She also gave me money
for a taxi.

10:05.928 --> 10:07.260
I hate you!

10:07.262 --> 10:08.495
I know, right?!

10:08.497 --> 10:09.796
How was your day?

10:09.798 --> 10:11.698
I'm pretty sure
Lyndsey and I broke up.

10:11.700 --> 10:14.968
Oh, man, I'm sorry.

10:16.171 --> 10:18.038
I really liked Lyndsey.
I thought she was great.

10:18.040 --> 10:20.274
Yeah, well, she is great,
but I'm not gonna be bullied

10:20.276 --> 10:22.109
into spending the rest of my
life with somebody

10:22.111 --> 10:23.277
just 'cause they're great.

10:23.279 --> 10:26.314
Who would? It's like being
forced to win the lotto.

10:26.316 --> 10:27.915
Wait a minute.

10:27.917 --> 10:31.285
If you took a cab home,
where's my car?

10:32.354 --> 10:33.988
Huh.

10:35.324 --> 10:37.859
Here's a hundred bucks.
Buy a better car.

10:40.696 --> 10:42.663
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

10:43.665 --> 10:45.533
So, you ready
for round two?

10:45.535 --> 10:47.668
Oh, right now?

10:47.670 --> 10:52.839
Could we just talk a little
while the boys,

10:52.841 --> 10:55.808
you know,
restock the shelves?

10:55.810 --> 10:59.612
Yeah, sure, let's talk.

10:59.614 --> 11:03.549
Um, how are things
going with your book?

11:03.551 --> 11:05.685
How's... with the what?

11:05.687 --> 11:07.187
Your book.

11:07.189 --> 11:08.588
The one you're
trying to finish?

11:08.590 --> 11:10.624
Oh, my... the book.

11:11.759 --> 11:13.927
Good.

11:13.929 --> 11:15.395
It's good.

11:15.397 --> 11:17.998
It's going good.

11:18.000 --> 11:21.802
Writing words.

11:21.804 --> 11:23.971
Making sentences.

11:23.973 --> 11:25.772
What's it about?

11:25.774 --> 11:28.909
Okay, um... yeah.
It's about this, uh...

11:28.911 --> 11:32.747
guy named Alan.

11:32.749 --> 11:34.849
Mm-hmm.

11:34.851 --> 11:37.152
He... and he lives
with his brother

11:37.154 --> 11:41.756
in this, uh, fabulous
Malibu beach house.

11:41.758 --> 11:44.358
And?

11:45.227 --> 11:49.564
And... the brother dies.

11:49.566 --> 11:52.767
He falls in front
of a train in Paris.

11:52.769 --> 11:54.535
Wow.

11:54.537 --> 11:55.903
Didn't see that coming.

11:56.772 --> 11:58.940
Neither did he.

12:03.445 --> 12:08.883
Anyway, this, uh, this
billionaire named Wal... ter...

12:08.885 --> 12:12.519
comes along and
he buys the house,

12:12.521 --> 12:15.656
and then, and Alan
continues to live there.

12:15.658 --> 12:18.158
Wait. With a
complete stranger?

12:18.160 --> 12:20.060
Yeah.

12:20.062 --> 12:21.995
Are they gay?

12:21.997 --> 12:24.197
No. No, no.

12:24.199 --> 12:27.100
No, they're just...
they're just friends.

12:27.102 --> 12:29.302
That's a bit far-fetched,
isn't it?

12:29.304 --> 12:31.604
What? No.

12:31.606 --> 12:33.573
That's totally plausible.

12:35.210 --> 12:38.613
They have these...
adventures together.

12:40.216 --> 12:42.250
It's funny.

12:42.252 --> 12:46.555
It's a good thing
you're pretty.

12:50.560 --> 12:52.861
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

12:54.364 --> 12:55.564
Hey.

12:55.566 --> 12:57.767
Whoa.

12:59.836 --> 13:01.971
Look at you.
Bought some new clothes, huh?

13:01.973 --> 13:03.806
Nope.

13:03.808 --> 13:05.941
Somebody bought new clothes
for me.

13:07.109 --> 13:10.312
Shari took her boy toy
shopping in Beverly Hills.

13:10.314 --> 13:13.581
I felt like Julia Roberts
in <i>Pretty Woman.</i>

13:16.752 --> 13:18.587
The only thing I got
from the truck driver

13:18.589 --> 13:21.657
was a pack of cigarettes
and an eyebrow pencil.

13:21.659 --> 13:23.225
Yeah, I gotta tell you,

13:23.227 --> 13:25.929
it is nice to be taken
care of for a change. Well...

13:25.931 --> 13:29.132
Look who I'm talkin' to.

13:29.134 --> 13:31.768
All right, I'm gonna go
do some manscaping.

13:31.770 --> 13:34.872
Mama like me smooth.

13:36.509 --> 13:37.775
Oh, hey, buddy.

13:37.777 --> 13:39.977
Hey, Dad.
Well, this is a nice surprise.

13:39.979 --> 13:41.278
What's going on?

13:41.280 --> 13:43.848
Well, I heard from Eldridge
that you and his mom broke up,

13:43.850 --> 13:45.316
so I'm just checking in
to see how you're doing.

13:45.318 --> 13:47.485
That is really sweet
of you, Jake,

13:47.487 --> 13:49.053
to be concerned
about your old man.

13:49.055 --> 13:51.592
Well, I love you, Dad.
I want you to be happy.

13:51.617 --> 13:52.558
Thank you.

13:52.559 --> 13:54.226
And, you know, you've always
been there for me.

13:54.228 --> 13:55.961
Now I get to be here for you.

13:55.963 --> 13:57.196
That's true.

13:57.198 --> 14:00.733
Speaking of which...
How much?

14:00.735 --> 14:03.236
A couple hundred bucks would
make it a Merry Christmas

14:03.238 --> 14:04.571
for all the people I love.

